 |><| 𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣𝙣𝙚𝙧 𝙨𝙘𝙖𝙣𝙣𝙚𝙧 = 𝙣𝙚𝙬 𝙎𝙘𝙖𝙣𝙣𝙚𝙧(𝙎𝙮𝙨𝙩𝙚𝙢.𝙞𝙣); |><|
               \/
           Object Name

      >> You can name the object anything.
      >> Here is Scanner.
      >> Apply the method as name of object.
      >> Scanner scanner = new Scanner
           :: Code = scanner.nextDatatype

       >> If you can change the object name.
       >> Scanner sc = new Scanner
           :: Code = sc.nextDatatype

   :|: You can check below how i apply with sc object.
   ________________________________________________________________
   | 𝐃𝐚𝐭𝐚 𝐓𝐲𝐩𝐞 |><|    𝐌𝐞𝐭𝐡𝐨𝐝      |><|     𝐄𝐱𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐞              |
   |"""""""""""""|"""""""""""""""""""|""""""""""""""""""""""""""""|
   |    byte     |    nextByte()     |  byte b = sc.nextByte();   |   
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    short    |    nextShort()    |  short s = sc.nextShort(); |  
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    int      |    nextint()      |  int i = sc.nextInt();     |
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    long     |    nextLong()     |  long l = sc.nextLong();   |
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    float    |    nextFloat()    |  float f = sc.nextFloat(); |  
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    double   |    nextDouble()   | double d = sc.nextDouble();|
   |-------------|-------------------|----------------------------|
   |    String   |    next()         |  String s = sc.next();      \
   |-------------|-------------------|------------------------------\
   |    boolean  |    nextboolean()  |  Bolean b = sc.nextBoolean(); \
   |-------------|-------------------|--------------------------------|
   |    char     |next().charAt(num) |  char c = sc.next().charAt(2)  |
   |-------------|-------------------|--------------------------------|
   |'''''''''''''|'''''''''''''''''''|''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''|

